sp.p:
After the Dance was over, King Herod with a great deal of Majesty came to the Damosel, and in the following Rhymes (which the Curate of the Parish compos'd upon that occasion, and I have since translated) thus complemented her;


Well hast thou danc'd Illustrious Maid,

I like thy graceful motion;

Ask what thou wilt, and by my Soul

'Tis all at thy devotion.
